name: .LIST File Extension
summary: Learn about .LIST files and view a list of programs that open them.

description: FIle created by APT, an Advanced Package Tool used to manage applications; holds a list of package sources that software can be downloaded from; contains information detailing the archive type indicating whether it contains binary or source packages.

content: The LIST file typically follows this format: deb http://host/debian distribution section1 section2 section3 deb-src http://host/debian distribution section1 section2 section3
The first word of each line notifies the archive type:
deb means that it holds a binary package.
deb-src means that it holds a source package.
NOTE: The APT tool is found within the Debian operating system.
